Thanks for all the memories of our firefighting together.




			
				
				Posted by: rollin kerzee - lima,  OH - friend   Feb 25, 2013
			










To the Truex Family, 
Sorry for your loss. The Truex "name" was mentioned alot in our house when I was growing up. ....you see my father, was Mr. Ron Dotson, track coach, at Lima Central High and then Lima Senior High.  My father always talked and sang praises for the Truexes.  
My sympathies to the you all.  
Your truly,
Linda Dotson Seidman, daughter of Ron Dotson




			
				
				Posted by: Linda Dotson Seidman - Germantown,  TN   Feb 22, 2013
			












May you rest in peace. Will never forget the many visits and seeing the turtles and all of the wild life on the pond or the sword fish on the wall. Love always Kathy




			
				
				Posted by: Kathy Browne Dickson - lima,  OH - Uncle   Feb 21, 2013
			










Family, friends and past coworkers of Mr. Truex,
I grew up knowing Mr. Truex through the fire department family. My father, Captain Robert D. Huber, worked with Mr. Truex on the fire department where I met him in my youth. He was a man of many talents. Please accept my condolences on his passing. This world will be a lot less colorful without Mr. Truex in it.
Respectfully,




			
				
				Posted by: Tom Huber -  TX   Feb 21, 2013
			







